Seasonal temperature changes in Arctic Alaska

1 Overview

This project seeks to answer the following research question:

Is Arctic shrubification controlled by winter or summer temperatures?

1.1 Research Questions:

This analysis is composed of four subquestions:

  1. How has the mean July temperature of Arctic Alaska changed over the past 39 years (1979-2018)?

  2. How has the mean January temperature of Arctic Alaska changed over the past 39 years?

  3. Have winter or summer temperatures changed more over the study period?

  4. Are there any observable patterns of shrub expansion that can be explained by changes in winter or summer temperatures?

1.2 Rationale:

  • High latitude regions are projected to warm at twice the rate of the global average (IPCC 2013)
  • Permafrost thaw releases greenhouse gases & contributes to more warming
  • Shrubs are expanding & contribute to climate feedback cycles
    • Taller shrubs store more carbon - less carbon in atmosphere
    • Taller shrubs trap snow - soil is warmer during winter - increases permafrost thaw
  • In order to model changes in vegetation and climate we need a thorough understanding of ecosystem processes
  • However, the controls on shrub expansion are not well understood

1.3 Data:

NCEP North American Regional Reanalysis (NARR) monthly temperature at 2m height (air.2m.mon.mean)

Source: NCEP Reanalysis data provided by the NOAA/OAR/ESRL PSD, Boulder, Colorado, USA, from their Web site at https://www.esrl.noaa.gov/psd/

Note: this analysis was initally conducted using NCEP North American Regional Reanalysis (NARR) monthly temperature at 2m height, however the current dataset was ultimately selected because the NARR data is projected on an irregular grid causing difficulties for spatial analysis. ***

1.4 Methodology:

  • Load and project shapefiles: World, Alaska, Alaskan Arctic
  • Load NetCDF4 File
  • Project temperature data
  • Plot long term mean temperature by month
  • Select region of interest and extract data
  • Index plot of January temperatures
  • Index plot of July temperatures
  • Box plot of mean temperature change
  • Load shapefile of shrub expansion
  • Heatmap of seasonal temperature changes
  • Evaluate pattern of climatic and vegetation change

1.5 Current road-blocks & troubleshooting efforts:

  • Extracting data from ncdf based upon shapefile extent
  • Analyzing regional change in temperature over time (need extracted data)
  • Overlaying shapefile-derived map boundaries on plots (& maps libarary doesn’t have AK map)
  • Loading geotiff file

2 Load and project shapefiles

# read the world shapefile
shp_path <- "/Users/Ori/Documents/REarthSysSci/gis/"
shp_name <- "ne_110m_admin_0_countries.shp"
shp_file <- paste(shp_path, shp_name, sep="")
world_shp <- read_sf(shp_file)
world_outline <- as(st_geometry(world_shp), Class="Spatial")

# read the Arctic shapefile
shp_name <- "alaska_arctic.shp"
shp_file <- paste(shp_path, shp_name, sep="")
arctic_shp <- read_sf(shp_file)
arctic_outline <- as(st_geometry(arctic_shp), Class="Spatial")

# read the Alaska shapefile
shp_name <- "alaska.shp"
shp_file <- paste(shp_path, shp_name, sep="")
alaska_shp <- read_sf(shp_file)
alaska_outline <- as(st_geometry(alaska_shp), Class="Spatial")

#project shapefiles

ak.proj <- "+proj=aea +lat_1=55 +lat_2=65 +lat_0=50 +lon_0=-154 +x_0=0 +y_0=0 +ellps=GRS80 +datum=NAD83 +units=m +no_defs"
arctic_proj <- spTransform(arctic_outline, CRS(ak.proj))
proj4string(world_outline) <- CRS("+proj=longlat")
## Warning in `proj4string<-`(`*tmp*`, value = new("CRS", projargs = "+proj=longlat +ellps=WGS84")): A new CRS was assigned to an object with an existing CRS:
## +proj=longlat +datum=WGS84 +no_defs +ellps=WGS84 +towgs84=0,0,0
## without reprojecting.
## For reprojection, use function spTransform
world_proj <- spTransform(world_outline, CRS(ak.proj))
alaska_proj <- spTransform(alaska_outline, CRS(ak.proj))

# plot with outlines, a better color scale

plt + latticeExtra::layer(sp.lines(world_proj, col="gray30", lwd=0.5))+ latticeExtra::layer(sp.lines(arctic_proj, col="gray30", lwd=0.5))

# Extract temperature data from Arctic Alaska

#subset the temperature data to focus on Arctic Alaska
arctic_buffer <- st_buffer(arctic_shp, dist = 75000)
arctic_buffer_proj<-st_set_crs(arctic_buffer, CRS(ak.proj))
## Warning: st_crs<- : replacing crs does not reproject data; use st_transform for that
arctic_buffer_proj<-as(st_geometry(arctic_buffer_proj), Class="Spatial")
arctic_buffer_proj <- spTransform(arctic_buffer_proj, CRS(ak.proj))

tmp_arctic<-mask(tmp_proj, arctic_buffer_proj)
#rasterVis plot
mapTheme <- rasterTheme(region = rev(brewer.pal(10, "RdBu")))
cutpts <- c(-50,-40,-30,-20,-10,0,10,20,30,40,50)
plt <- levelplot(subset(tmp_arctic,1), margin = F, at=cutpts, cuts=11, pretty=TRUE, par.settings = mapTheme,
  main="January 1979 temperature")
plt + latticeExtra::layer(sp.lines(world_proj, col="black", lwd=1.0))+ latticeExtra::layer(sp.lines(arctic_proj, col="black", lwd=1.0))
